# Cline rules for blenderized-tubefeed-calculator

1. Read CONTEXT.md §9 (Current status) FIRST. Trust its checkboxes —
   do not re-do or re-verify completed phases.

2. The backend (Phases 2–5: data_loader, models, calculator, measures,
   targets, report) is COMPLETE and VERIFIED as of 2026-07-15.
   Do not rewrite, re-scaffold, or re-test these modules unless the
   user explicitly asks or a change breaks them.

3. To verify the backend, run:

   .venv/bin/python scripts/verify_backend.py

   It exits 0 and prints "=== ALL BACKEND MODULES VERIFIED ===" on
   success. If you add backend features, extend that script instead of
   writing a new one-off verification command.

4. Current work: Phase 6 (app/streamlit_app.py) is scaffolded and
   backend-verified — remaining work is Week 3 scope (pytest suite, CI,
   Streamlit Cloud deploy, USDA SR Legacy supplement) plus the pinned
   issues in CONTEXT.md §9. See CONTEXT.md §1 for the app flow and §6
   for the build plan.

5. Never modify anything under cnf_fcen_all-files-data_2026/ (raw data).

6. After completing meaningful work, update CONTEXT.md §9 status and
   commit, so the next session starts from accurate state.
